<br><br>

<<He>> looks away once more. "I won't insist upon you. I know this is a lot, but it would be easier with someone like you by my side. Someone to share this <span class="blue">burden</span> with.
It's a selfish desire. I offer nothing in return, because I have nothing to give. This isn't a request or a service. It's thankless work, which one must tolerate, learn to enjoy, or... abandon."
<br><br>

<<He>> sinks further into the water. "There's no hard feelings if you refuse. I just hope this doesn't scare you off for good."
<br><br>

<<He>> stays quiet for a while.
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Gwylan Ritual Bait End Wash 3]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Ritual Bait End Wash 3
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

<<if $worn.neck.name is "familiar collar" and $worn.neck.cursed is 1>>
	<<He>> runs <<his>> hands along your collar affectionately. It makes you feel warm. <<trauma -6>><<ltrauma>>
	<<detach_leash>>
	<br><br>
<<elseif $phase2 is "collar">>
	<<set $beastRitual.collared to false>><<set $beastRitual.leash to false>>
	<<set $worn.neck.type.push("broken")>><<neckruined true>>
	<<storeonneck "gwylanRitual">><<generalUndress "wardrobe" "neck">>
	<<neckwear 21>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"Do you mind if I keep your collar? I like it," you say shyly.
		<<case "bratty">>
			"Can I keep this collar? It's growing on me," you say.
		<<default>>
			"Can I keep this collar?" you ask.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	Gwylan blinks, then giggles. "If you really want to, dear. I've got plenty more if you lose it." <<Hes>> trying to hide it, but <<he>> seems pleased.
	<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("familiar_collar")>>
