	<</if>>
	<br><br>
<<elseif $beastRitual.collared is true>>
	<<set $worn.neck.type.push("broken")>><<neckruined true>>
	"Ah, before I forget..." <<He>> reaches around your neck and removes your collar. <<He>> spins it around on <<his>> finger for a moment before placing it outside the bath.
	<br><br>
<<elseif $beastRitual.leash is true>>
	"Ah, before I forget..." <<He>> reaches around your neck and removes your leash. <<He>> whips it in the air a few times before placing it outside the bath.
	<<detach_leash>>
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<if $beastRitual.purgeInfo>>
	<<set $beastRitual.purge += Math.floor($beastRitual.purgeInfo.fluid / 10)>>
	<<set $beastRitual.purge += Math.floor($beastRitual.purgeInfo.banish / 20)>>
<</if>>
<<if $beastRitual.ejac and ($beastRitual.hasScent or $beastRitual.isScent)>>
	<<set $beastRitual.purge++>>
<</if>>

<<if ["thunderStorm"].includes(Weather.name)>>
	The lull of the thunder leads the trees in a windy dance, yet you two remain untouched by the storm.
<<elseif ["lightPrecipitation", "heavyPrecipitation"].includes(Weather.name)>>
	The smell of the <<= Weather.precipitation>> is soothing, too.
<<elseif ["heavyClouds"].includes(Weather.name)>>
	You and Gwylan watch the forest dance in the wind.
<<elseif Time.dayState is "dusk">>
	The two of you watch the forest dance in the hues of sunset.
<<else>>
	The two of you enjoy the silence of the forest, basking in <<if Time.dayState is "night">>moonlight<<else>>the sun<</if>>.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<if $beastRitual.purge gte 5>>
	"<span class="green">We did very well today.</span> I can already feel it. I couldn't have done it without your help, either."
<<elseif $beastRitual.purge gte 3>>
	"<span class="teal">We did well today.</span> The forest is a little cleaner."
<<elseif $beastRitual.purge gte 1>>
	"<span class="blue">It wasn't much, but we surely purged some of the poison.</span> More than what I can accomplish alone, too."
<<else>>
	"<span class="purple">We didn't do well,</span> but it could have been worse. We just have to keep trying."
<</if>>
<<if $beastRitual.purge gte 1>>
	<<earnFeat "First Verse">>
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> looks out to the forest, tapping a finger on the side of the tub.
<br><br>

<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("struggles") and !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_sex_intro") and !_gwylanStatus.includes("cautious")>>
	<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("ritual_sex_intro")>>
	"There's something I wanted to talk to you about," <<he>> starts. "It's important." <<He>> doesn't turn to look at you.
	<br><br>

	<<if $gwylanTalked.includes("temple_confessor")>>
		"There's one thing the cloister is right about. The most effective way to purge is between two humans.
	<<else>>
		"The most effective cleansing method is between two humans.
	<</if>>
	However, it's also the most dangerous. Not just because humans are more dangerous themselves, but because the effectiveness is so great that it can harm the recipient of the poison if care isn't taken.
	It can be... difficult to stop once the transfer has begun." <<He>> sighs.
	<<if $gwylanTalked.includes("temple_confessor")>>
		"Besides that, I can't use the same method as the confessors. I'm not... one of them.
	<<else>>
		"Besides that, the setup is complex.
	<</if>>
	I'm out of practice, too. A connection to the forest is still needed for both participants, and it's more intense than this one. <span class="blue">It involves becoming a vessel for the forest itself.</span>"
	<br><br>

	<<He>> finally turns to you, and starts speaking faster. "What I'm trying to say is, I haven't had intercourse with another human in a long time, and I trust you enough that I..." <<His>> face turns bright red.
	"There's no easy way to say this, so let me just say it. <span class="pink">I want to have sex with you, and use the resulting connection to cleanse the forest</span>." <<npcincr Gwylan lust 1>><<glust>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> takes a deep breath. "It's not a boundary that comes easy to cross, because I don't wish for things between us to change.
	<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_corruption_share_intimate")>>
		I've already told you that things between us can't become more intimate, and that holds true.
	<</if>>
	Becoming fluid-bonded with someone can lead to complicated emotions, so it's important that you understand that this doesn't mean you and I are..." <<He>> points between you and <<him>> repeatedly.
	"More than friends. <span class="purple">Sex isn't love, and love isn't sex.</span> With everything you've told me, I trust you to understand.
	Still, <span class="lewd">fluid transfer would be mandatory, and there mustn't be any obstructions</span>."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> sinks into the water. "We don't have to, of course. We can keep going as we have been, or come back to our current method at any time. We have a week to think about it."
	<<He>> quickly stands up, covering <<himself>> with a towel and tossing you a few.

<<else>>

	<<if $beastRitual.tainted>>
		"Our quarry was particularly tainted. <span class="blue">More like them will show up as the poison takes root.</span>
		Luckily, as things are now, beings like that are often chased away by their peers. It keeps them isolated and safe until we can find them.
		Like many dying beasts, they prefer to crawl away and wither alone, preserving their dignity.
		However, if things get worse... much, much worse than they could get now, they may start to show up out in the open." <<His>> fingers trace shapes on the surface of the water.
		<br><br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $beastRitual.purgeInfo>>
		<<if Math.floor($beastRitual.purgeInfo.banish / 20) gte 1>>
			"That radiance. Your radiance. <span class="gold">It was brilliant</span>, but I don't believe less tainted dryads would be affected by it. Still, it's a boon." <<His>> eyes trace something above your head.
			<br>
		<</if>>
		<<if Math.floor($beastRitual.purgeInfo.fluid / 10) gte 1>>
			"Of course, <span class="blue">the more fluid we can extract, the more effective it will be</span>. Most animals only have so much to give, though. The dryads are a special case." <<He>> stares at the stains of nectar on the ground where you tended to the plantperson.
			<br>
		<</if>>
	<</if>>
	<<if $beastRitual.ejac and ($beastRitual.hasScent or $beastRitual.isScent)>>
		"There was a compatibility between you. <span class="blue">Purging is most effective between the same species,</span> but none of the forest's natural denizens have the capability to do so without human intervention.
		It's a poison we made, and one we must cleanse.
		<<if $fox gte 6 and $beastRitual.lure is "fox">>
			You're still more human than you are fox,
		<<elseif $dryad gte 6 and $beastRitual.lure is "dryad">>
			You're still more human than you are dryad,
		<<else>>
			You're still more human than you are wolf,
		<</if>>
		but there's no doubt it made our ritual more effective." <<He>> smiles at you. "I'm lucky to have you here." <<He>> leans back, watching the sky.
	<<else>>
		"Purging is most effective between the same species, but none of the forest's natural denizens have the capability to do so without human intervention.
		It's a poison we made, and one we must cleanse." <<He>> leans back, watching the sky.
	<</if>>
	<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_sex")>>
		"I don't mind continuing to use this method. I know the more intimate version of the ritual can be too much."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<if $beastRitual.tendingSuccess>>
		"Even just having an extra pair of capable hands makes a big difference.
		<<if $beastRitual.lure is "dryad">>
			Thanks to you, <span class="blue">I was able to prune much more of the dryad's tainted leaves.</span>"
		<<else>>
			Thanks to you, <span class="blue">we were able to make sure they were clean both inside and out.</span>"
		<</if>>
	<<else>>
		"It's important to make sure they're clean inside and out. <span class="purple">Unfortunately, we didn't quite manage that.</span> It's alright. I'm sure you'll become better with your hands if you keep up work like this."
	<</if>>
	<<He>> looks over the side of the tub at something. "On that note, we're plenty clean on the outside. It's time for me to get dirty on the inside." <<He>> stands and wraps a towel around <<his>> waist, stepping out of the tub.

	<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
		"You can leave if you wish, although I wouldn't mind the company."
	<<else>>
		"Your part here is done. You may leave. Thank you for your help."
	<</if>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<set $beastRitual.purgeInverse to $beastRitual.purge * -1>>
<<world_corruption "soft" $beastRitual.purgeInverse>>
<<set $gwylan.purged += $beastRitual.purge>>
<<if $gwylan.request.event is "meetAtShop">>
