:: Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_stay")>>
	<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("ritual_stay")>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"Can I stay with you, please?" you ask.
		<<case "bratty">>
			"No, I think I'll stay actually," you say.
		<<default>>
			"Since you gave me a choice, I think I'll stay," you say.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> looks surprised, but smiles. "You're certainly welcome to." <<He>> gestures to a raised section of the garden, retained by a stone ledge. You sit down on it.
<<else>>
	You wordlessly follow Gwylan and sit on the stone ledge.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> sits down, <<if _gwylanStatus.includes("lust")>>still topless<<else>>now robed<</if>>, next to you.
<<if $beastRitual.lure is "dryad">>
	<<set $beastRitual.poisonAmount to 1>>
	<<if $beastRitual.tendingSuccess>>
		<<set $beastRitual.poisonAmount++>>
	<</if>>
	<<if $beastRitual.tainted>>
		<<set $beastRitual.poisonAmount++>>
	<</if>>

	<<He>> holds the bucket full of tainted plantperson foliage.
	<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_corruption_dryad")>>
		<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("ritual_corruption_dryad")>>
		"The fun part is over, this is the miserable bit." You watch as <<he>> picks up an antique salt shaker, unscrews the top, and dumps the entire thing into the bucket. <<He>> then shakes the bucket around.
		<br><br>

		<<switch $speech_attitude>>
			<<case "meek">>
				"Wait, what are you—" you start to ask.
			<<case "bratty">>
				"Uhh... what—" you start.
			<<default>>
				"What in the world are you—" you start to ask.
		<</switch>>
		You don't get the chance to finish. <<He>> pulls one of the dead leaves from the bucket, now covered in salt, and <span class="purple">eats it</span>. It sounds crunchy. <<stress 3>><<gstress>>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> turns to you and smiles after swallowing. "Yes, it's vile. That's what the salt is for. It masks most of the taste." <<He>> reaches in, and eats another one.
		<br><br>

		"Why?" you ask.
		<br><br>

		<<He>> holds up a finger as <<he>> chews. This one seems much less pleasant than the first. <<He>> reaches for a small glass of water right next to you, which you didn't see when you sat down.
		<<He>> drinks it, forcing <<himself>> to swallow the leaf. "Sorry. The crunchy ones aren't so bad, it's the chewy ones that really make me want to vomit."
		<br><br>

		You stare at <<him>> for a moment. "Oh! You meant why am I eating them. Well. They're tainted. If I leave them to decay, their poison will just leak back into the world. I can't let a single leaf, petal or thorn rot away."
		<<He>> makes a sinking gesture with <<his>> hands. <<He>> eats another. "Sometimes I dry them and use them as seasoning on my crepes. Sometimes I just salt them, like this.
		The thorns are capable of injecting the poison like a stinger, so for those, I simply..." <<He>> pulls one out of the bucket, and <span class="red">sticks it into <<his>> skin</span>. <<stress 12>><<ggstress>>
		<br><br>

		<<if $beastRitual.tainted>>
			"As for the whole vine we had to amputate, that has to be consumed too.
		<<else>>
			"When dryads get particularly tainted, some of their vines can become oversaturated. If those vines can't be purged, they'll have to be amputated and consumed, too.
		<</if>>
		I typically chop them up and use them in various dishes over the span of the week. It's easier on me if I don't do it all at once." <<He>> pulls the thorn back out of <<his>> skin. It's a noticeably lighter shade now.
		"I'm quite used to it. I have a routine, after all." <<He>> looks away from you. "Not that I particularly mind having that routine changed. I'm glad you're here, and grateful you chose to stay."
	<<else>>
		<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("request_gold_accessories") and !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_poison_talk")>>
			<<He>> kicks <<his>> feet, examining a drained thorn. "Do you remember what I told you about people trying to imbibe poison to extend their lives?"
			<br><br>

			You nod.
			<br><br>

			<<He>> crushes the thorn, brittle now that it's empty. "Do you think there could be any truth to it?" <<He>> turns to you and gives you a sly smile, not waiting for your answer.
			<br><br>
		<</if>>

		<<He>> dumps half of an antique salt shaker into the bucket and begins to pick out leaves and flower petals to consume. "Thank you for sticking around again," <<he>> says.
		"Having someone to talk to helps keep my mind off of how rotten this makes me feel inside."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Relax and chat with Gwylan|Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Relax]]>><<stress -2>><<trauma -2>><</link>><<lstress>><<ltrauma>>
	<br>
	<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_corruption_share")>>
		<<link [[Offer to eat some of the poison|Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Share]]>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>>
	<<else>>
		<<link [[Offer to eat some of the poison|Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Share]]>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>><<gyearning>>
	<</if>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	<<set $beastRitual.poisonAmount to $beastRitual.purge - $beastRitual.purgeDirect>>
	<<He>> holds the small ivory bowl.
	<<if $beastRitual.poisonAmount gte 5>>
		It's nearly overflowing with a glowing pink liquid.
	<<elseif $beastRitual.poisonAmount gte 3>>
		It's full of a glowing pink liquid.
	<<elseif $beastRitual.poisonAmount gte 1>>
		It's half-filled with a glowing pink liquid.
	<<else>>
		There's a small amount of pink liquid inside of it.
	<</if>>
	<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_corruption_beast")>>
		<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("ritual_corruption_beast")>>
		"Medicine for the world," <<he>> says, bringing the bowl to <<his>> lips. <<He>> drinks all of it.
		<br><br>

		<<He>> sits still for a moment, before <span class="purple">shuddering harshly and leaning forward</span>.
		<br><br>

		<<if $temple_confessor_intro>>
			You know from your time in the confessional that it's nothing to worry about, but you rub <<his>> back for comfort. You know how rotten it feels.
		<<else>>
			You're not sure what to do, so you rub <<his>> back for comfort.
		<</if>>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> sits up straight again, giving you a smile. "I'm alright, don't worry about me. This is what it takes to drain the poison from the world." <<He>> takes a moment to catch <<his>> breath.
		<br><br>

		"It takes two things. A stable vessel," <<he>> starts, pointing to <<himself>> with one hand and putting the other on your tummy. "And an area immunised to the poison." <<He>> spreads <<his>> arms out wide to gesture to the whole garden.
		It almost seems to grow as <<he>> does so. "It's what makes it so virulent. Even if a tainted creature dies, it will all just leak out again. It defies the natural cycle. But, if you get both of those things, you can trap it in your body."
		<<He>> holds up the bowl. It's covered in intricate carvings and symbols. "The bowl is for the leftovers. Any poison that doesn't end up in your body at the moment of climax gets captured in here instead."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> sets the bowl aside, leaning back. "Thank you for staying. Talking keeps my mind off of it while it settles."
		<br><br>

		<<link [[Relax and chat with Gwylan|Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Relax]]>><<set $phase to 1>><<stress -2>><<trauma -2>><</link>><<lstress>><<ltrauma>>
		<br>
	<<else>>
		<br><br>

		<<link [[Relax and chat with Gwylan|Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Relax]]>><<stress -2>><<trauma -2>><</link>><<lstress>><<ltrauma>>
		<br>
		<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_corruption_share")>>
			<<link [[Offer to drink half of the poison|Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Share]]>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>>
		<<else>>
			<<link [[Offer to drink half of the poison|Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Share]]>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>><<gyearning>>
		<</if>>
	<</if>>
<</if>>

:: Gwylan Ritual Bait Corruption Share
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $beastRitual.sharedBurden to true>>
<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_corruption_share")>>
	<<if $temple_confessor_intro>>
		<<switch $speech_attitude>>
			<<case "meek">>
